“Our livelihood as commercial fishermen depends on the salmon that we don’t catch in our net just as much as the ones that we do. We take care of our wild salmon fishery so that it continues to thrive for years and years to come.” 

Michael and Nelly Hand own and operate @driftersfish, in Cordova, Alaska. Check out our story to learn more about their operation and how they work with the Alaska Department of Fish & Game to catch healthy, wild caught salmon for their customers while using science to maintain the species population in their fishery. Photos: @luciannamcintosh
